s of three lines of the upper part of an inscription.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Elegant and regular v-cut monumental letters. Manganaro notes that the letter-forms are identical across the two fragments.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Line 1-2\u003C/locus>\u003C!-- Manganaro -->\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"70\" atMost=\"70\">70\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270\">Catina\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2525068\">Catania\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.49223, 15.07041\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julia